	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-10-16T10:32:02">Schroder UK Mid Cap Fund Plc is a United Kingdom-based investment company. The Company's investment objective is to invest in mid cap equities, with the aim of providing a total return in excess of the financial times stock exchange (FTSE) 250 (ex-investment companies) Index. The Company targets investment opportunities in medium-sized the United Kingdom companies. The Company is engaged in investing in sectors, such as financials, consumer services, consumer goods, oil and gas, industrials, basic materials, technology, utilities, healthcare, telecommunications and liquid assets. The liquid assets consist of cash, deposits and money market instruments with maturities of around 397 days. The Company's strategy is to invest principally in the investment universe associated with the benchmark index. The Company invests in smaller companies. Its investment manager is Schroder Investment Management Limited. The Company's alternative investment fund manager is Schroder Unit Trusts Limited.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-22T23:44:47">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 30 September 2015, Schroder UK Mid &amp; Small Cap Fund plc revenues decreased 6% to L15.7M. Net income decreased 3% to L14M. Revenues reflect Realized G/L on Investments Securities decrease of 94% to L512K, Other interest receivable and similar in decrease of 80% to L3K. Net income also reflects Directors' fees increase of 22% to L128K (expense), Secretarial fee increase of 3% to L120K (expense).</Text>
